[I] Perl module for accesing the web

[T] The libwww-perl collection is a set of Perl modules which provides a
[T] simple and consistent application programming interface to the
[T] World-Wide Web. The main focus of the library is to provide classes
[T] and functions that allow you to write WWW clients. The library also
[T] contain modules that are of more general use and even classes that
[T] help you implement simple HTTP servers.

